Package problem01.controller

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    IParser
    Interface describing the public functionality of a Parser object, comprising of the ability to parse CLI arguments.
    ITaskManager
    Interface describing the public functionality of a Task object, including the ability generate an assortment of tasks (add To-do, complete To-do, display To-do), as well as perform them.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddTodo
    A task for adding a to-do item.
    ArgConstants
    A class containing constants representing command line arguments
    CategoryIterator
    Iterator class which can be utilized to return all Todos (within a collection) of the same category as that provided.
    CompareDate
    Comparator class which can be utilized to sort all Todos, according to their date.
    ComparePriority
    Comparator class which can be utilized to sort all Todos, according to their priority.
    CompleteTodo
    A task for completing a to-do item.
    IncompleteIterator
    Iterator class which can be utilized to return all Todos (within a collection) that are considered "incomplete".
    IteratorFactory
    Class which makes use of the Factory pattern to produce Iterators meant to filter through collections of Todos, based on completeness or category.
    Main  
    Parser
    The Parser class is responsible for parsing command line arguments and passing the pertinent information to methods in the TaskManager for performing tasks.
    TaskManager
    Acts as an invoker class in the Command design pattern.
    Todo
    A To-do object containing all its relevant fields.
